data.content:
Created both files. Here's how it works:

- **`@typeparam TItem`** makes it generic — works with any item type.
- **Internal copy**: The `Items` setter calls `.ToList()`, so the original list is never mutated.
- **Move Up/Down** buttons swap adjacent items in the internal list, then fire `OnOrderChanged` with a **new copy** of the reordered list.
- Buttons are disabled at list boundaries (first item can't move up, last can't move down).

Usage matches your example:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private void HandleReorder(List<TaskItem> reordered)
    {
        tasks = reordered;
    }
}
```
